**Q1. [KTU University Exam – Dec 2023]**
**Differentiate between Checked and Unchecked Exceptions in Java. Give two examples of each.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

| Feature | Checked Exception | Unchecked Exception |
|---|---|---|
| Detection | At compile-time | At run-time |
| Parent class | `Exception` (not RuntimeException) | `RuntimeException` |
| Handling | **Mandatory** (try-catch or throws) | Optional |
| Cause | External resources | Programming logic errors |

**Examples:**
- **Checked:** `IOException`, `SQLException`, `ClassNotFoundException`, `FileNotFoundException` *(2 marks for 2 examples)*
- **Unchecked:** `ArithmeticException`, `NullPointerException`, `ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException` *(1 mark for examples)*

