### 5.3 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Rapid Revision Checklist)

> [!TIP]
> **🔥 HIGH-FREQUENCY KTU POINTS — MEMORIZE BEFORE EXAM:**

- ⭐ **5 Keywords:** `try`, `catch`, `throw`, `throws`, `finally` — name them in order.
- ⭐ **Root class:** All exceptions inherit from `java.lang.Throwable`.
- ⭐ **Two main branches:** `Error` (unrecoverable) and `Exception` (recoverable).
- ⭐ **Checked = Compile-time** (must handle); **Unchecked = Run-time** (optional).
- ⭐ **`throw` throws ONE object**; **`throws` DECLARES multiple types**.
- ⭐ **`finally` runs ALWAYS** except `System.exit(0)` or JVM crash.
- ⭐ **Catch ordering:** Subclass BEFORE parent (compiler enforced).
- ⭐ **One try → multiple catch + one finally** (max).
- ⭐ **Custom Checked Exception:** `extends Exception` (mandatory handling).
- ⭐ **Custom Unchecked Exception:** `extends RuntimeException` (optional handling).
- ⭐ **Call `super(message)`** in custom exception constructor to use `getMessage()`.
- ⭐ **Nested try** = try inside a try; inner exceptions handled first by inner catches.
- ⭐ **Unreachable catch** = compilation error if parent catch precedes subclass catch.
- ⭐ **Java Built-in Checked:** `IOException`, `SQLException`, `ClassNotFoundException`, `FileNotFoundException`, `InterruptedException`.
- ⭐ **Java Built-in Unchecked:** `ArithmeticException`, `NullPointerException`, `ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException`, `NumberFormatException`, `ClassCastException`, `IndexOutOfBoundsException`.
- ⭐ **Java Built-in Errors:** `OutOfMemoryError`, `StackOverflowError`, `VirtualMachineError`.
- ⭐ **`try-with-resources`** (Java 7+): Auto-closes `AutoCloseable` resources in `finally` automatically.
- ⭐ **Method overriding rule:** Cannot throw new CHECKED exceptions beyond parent's `throws` clause.
- ⭐ **Empty catch block** is valid but considered bad practice — at least print/log the error.
- ⭐ **`getMessage()`** returns custom message; **`printStackTrace()`** prints full call chain.
- ⭐ **Every exception is an OBJECT** — created using `new ExceptionType("message")`.

